{% extends "_layouts/blog.jinja" %}

{% block page_content %}

<h3 id="intro">Intro</h3>
<p>
  Crystal is an exciting sounding language which is: 
  "As slick as Ruby and as fast as C."
</p>
<p>
  In this post I will show you how install the 
  {{ link::e(path="https://crystal-lang.org/", description="Crystal") }} programming 
  language on Ubuntu 2004.
</p>

<h4>Code versions used in this post</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Ubuntu - 2004</li>
  <li>Crystal - 1.1.0</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="crystal-repository">Crystal Repository</h3>
<p>
  First, add the Crystal repository to your apt sources.
</p>

{{ text::code_block(
  header="cmd",
  language="text",
  code="echo 'deb http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/devel:/languages:/crystal/xUbuntu_20.04/ /' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/devel:languages:crystal.list"
) }}


<h3 id="gpg-key">GPG Key</h3>
<p>
  Next, add the Crystal GPG key.
</p>

{{ text::code_block(
  header="cmd",
  language="text",
  code="curl -fsSL https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/devel:languages:crystal/xUbuntu_20.04/Release.key | gpg --dearmor | sudo tee /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/devel_languages_crystal.gpg > /dev/null"
) }}

<h3 id="install">Install</h3>
<p>
  With the pre-reqs out of the way, now its time to 
  install Crystal.
</p>
{{ text::code_block(
  header="cmd",
  language="text",
  code="sudo apt update -y && sudo apt install crystal -y"
) }}


<h3 id="verify">Verify</h3>
<p>
  Finally, verify the version of Crystal that is installed.
</p>

{{ text::code_block(
  header="cmd",
  language="text",
  code='crystal --version

# output

Crystal 1.1.0 [af095d72d] (2021-07-14)

LLVM: 10.0.1
Default target: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu'
) }}

<h3 id="outro">Outro</h3>
<p>
  With Crystal now installed, its time to start digging 
  into the language and eco-system.
</p>
{% endblock page_content %}